                <td bgColor="#ECECEC"><textarea cols="48" name="Message" rows="12" wrap="VIRTUAL" onselect="storeCaret(this);" onclick="storeCaret(this);" onkeyup="storeCaret(this);" onchange="storeCaret(this);">[quote][i]Originally posted by Oliar Corpsemaster[/i]
[br]I just started working on getting VT enabled.  My guild has decided to start doing Emp and VT again because there are times when we can't raid in PoP.

This guide is great so far.  I did steps 1-4 yesterday in a couple of hours.

10/25
1.  Dawnshroud Peaks:  I zoned in and there was an ooc about a shard rotting.  Looted Shard
2.  Scarlet Desert:  There was a level 55 mage hunting shards when I zoned in.  He said he had been there for hours.  I asked if he was killing all the shard mobs.  He said I could kill the ones in the back, since he couldn't kill them all.  Result:  2 kills, Shard dropped!!  I contemplated letting the poor mage loot the shard for about half a second, and then my greedy click button looted it for me.
3.  Maiden's Eye:  This took about 2 hours.  I killed the 3 camps near AR.  I did get adds occasionaly, but handled them without a problem.  The roamers in this zone make it challenging.
4.  The Grey:  Yawn, 3 kills and shard dropped.

I will start on number 5 today.

10/26
5. Katta/Seru:  I went to the Katta camp and killed 30 Centurions and no shard!!.    So since I was fed up with that, I went to Seru.  Got the Shard there on the walkway around the city in about 15 kills.  Pet tanked and dotted.

I went to Acrylia Caverns next (AR was camped).  AC is a little more challenging to get to camp.  I killed lots of bloodguards, but no shard yet.  Also, beware:  There are lots of casters here and it is hard to FD.  Might be better to have Levant memmed instead of FD, but I haven't changed that out yet myself.  Score:  AC 1  Oliar 0 on this one.  Will try again tomorrow.

10/27
Akhevia Ruins:  Follow the guide!!  Got the Shard.  But I didn't set off a trap.... hmmm.. oh well.

Fungus Grove:  Follow the guide!!  Got the shard on 2nd round of killing.

Acrylia Caverns:  Got the shard today.  Didn't Levant:  Acrylia Caverns 1  Oliar 1 !!

Went scouting the run in The Deep.  I had sow.  I used CoS and ran.   I ran into some see invis mobs, but kept click CoS on to reduce other aggro.   I used the ingame map and ran across the bridge with no problem where I Fd'ed.  Just to be safe I /q'ed out.  Killed a couple of Horrors, but I need to get to raid.  Will update tomorrow.

The Deep (I had time after all):  My hp is higher than some, so getting buffs are ok.  I did it self buffed.  I did it with SoW, Circlet of Shadow, and the ingame map.  Ran like hell, got aggro from see invis mob, kept clicking CoS, found invis bridge, used ingame map to walk across bridge(made it easy), got across and FD'ed.. /q'ed to make sure aggro gone.   Turn left, follow ledge til you see Horrors.  Kill and loot Shard.   Took me about 5 kills.

Time For SSRA!!!

10/28
Got the SSRA shard!!... but /sigh not solo.  Another guildmate needed shard, so I helped her and 2 dropped.

Let me straighten out the guide on this.  The camp is not the first camp on left where the torch is!!!!  There are 3 skele's there.   This is not the camp.  Continue going and you will see another torch on the wall on your right hand side (go left and follow tunnel.  Torch on right after seeing torch on left)  There are 2 skeles at that torch.   Follow the guide from there and you will be able to solo from that camp!!!

OK.  Tomorrow I will get the container in AR!!

10/29: AR Container

Do as the guide says and you'll be fine.  Just a couple of points.  

1) I had to go up the stairs where the 3 4armeds are and then jump down to the remains platform.

2) The South West remains is the one that aggros when you kill it.  Only 1 mob aggroed and you can easily FD with Forceshield up.

[/quote]</textarea><br /></td>
