                <td bgcolor="#ECECEC" valign="top" width="100" nowrap><font color="#000000" face="arial" size="2"><b>Ghoulia_Ghostbuster</b></font></td>
                <td bgcolor="#ECECEC" valign="top" width="100%"><font color="#000000" face="arial" size="2"><small>Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;10/22/2003&nbsp;: 05:42:30 AM</small><hr size="2"><span class="spnMessageText"> Graar's guide to shard farming<br /><br />This guide is not really authored by me. It's a compilation of information from this thread, with my own observations added:<br /><br /><a href="http://necro.eqclasses.com/forum/topic.asp?TOPIC_ID=22211" target="_blank">http://necro.eqclasses.com/forum/topic.asp?TOPIC_ID=22211</a><br /><br />--- The container ---<br /><br />You need this:<br />- Summoned wisp stone (ask your local mage, it's no rent)<br />- Essence emerald (from bazaar or your own local stash)<br /><br />Go to akheva. Invis up. Go to the altar with the sacrificed remains on it. On the way you'll probably set off some traps. When you do, FD, wait for the trap mobs to despawn, reinvis and move in. In the altar room, you'll see some shades, three fourarmed guys (above the altar). Stand on the altar, directly below the middle of the three four-armed guys. From here, you can uninvis without aggroing anything. Using a dd spell of some sort, kill the sacrificed remains untill a shimmering spirit spawns. Don't kill the remains furthest to the west, as nearby mobs will aggro. Hand wisp stone to the spirit. Hand essence emerald to the spirit. You will recieve a 10-slot container. Gate out.<br /><br /><a href="http://www.eqmaps.com/m3/akheva1.jpg" target="_blank">http://www.eqmaps.com/m3/akheva1.jpg</a> (appr. loc. 1100,-900)<br /><br />--- The shards (in order of difficulty) ---<br /><br />1. Dawnshroud Peaks<br /><br />Locate the rockhopper-cave (marked on map below). Kill rockhoppers untill you get a shard. This may take a while, but rockhoppers are easily killed. This shard is not often dropped, but should be possible to get within 3 hours or so.<br /><br /><a href="http://www.eqmaps.com/m3/dawnshroud2.gif" target="_blank">http://www.eqmaps.com/m3/dawnshroud2.gif</a><br /><br />References:<br /><br /><blockquote id="quote"><font size="2" face="arial" id="quote">quote:<hr height="1" noshade id="quote">This is the most easy shard there is, just let pet kill the rockhoppers and loot the shard when it drops. ( killed about 10 before the shard dropped)<hr height="1" noshade id="quote"></blockquote id="quote"></font id="quote"><br /><br />2. Scarlet desert<br /><br />Locate the plateu (marked on map as sun reaver temple). Kill Sun revenants and Sun reavers untill you get a shard. These are easily pet-tanked or aggro/fear-kited. This shard drops fairly often and should take less than 2 hours to obtain.<br /><br /><a href="http://www.eqmaps.com/m3/scarlet1.gif" target="_blank">http://www.eqmaps.com/m3/scarlet1.gif</a><br /><br />References:<br /><br /><blockquote id="quote"><font size="2" face="arial" id="quote">quote:<hr height="1" noshade id="quote">Well this one is also very easy, just pull the revenants on the mountaintop to the edge and root dot them. ( Killed 15 before shard drop)<hr height="1" noshade id="quote"></blockquote id="quote"></font id="quote"><br /><br />3. The grey<br /><br />Locate the little lake with skellies around it (NW part of map). Aggrokite them on the north zonewall. Shard here is also rare, but should be doable in max. 3-4 hours.<br /><br /><a href="http://www.eqmaps.com/m3/thegrey2.jpg" target="_blank">http://www.eqmaps.com/m3/thegrey2.jpg</a><br /><br />References:<br /><br /><blockquote id="quote"><font size="2" face="arial" id="quote">quote:<hr height="1" noshade id="quote">This camp is also kind of easy, pull with darkness, then run back on zonewall and dot the skellie, and then start agro kite with your pet, sow is a good thing here. Killed about 20 revenants before drop.<hr height="1" noshade id="quote"></blockquote id="quote"></font id="quote"><br /><br />4. Maidens eye<br /><br />This camp is a pain to say the least, it's not difficult, it's just boring. Very very boring. Around the zone, you'll find static goranga scouts. These are placeholders for the goranga seers, savants and profets. The easiest camp to find is the one near DSP entrance. There's three spawn spots (2 spots with three spawns, 1 with 2 spawns) near the entrance to Akheva as well, all of which (supposedly), have a chance to spawn a sharddropping mob (seer, savant, profet). Kill the scouts untill a shard mob pops (can take a looong time). Kill sharddropping mob and hope for the best. It took me 10 hours to get my shard, killing dsp entrance mobs (3 spawns) and the akheva mobs (2 + 3 + 3 mobs), constantly. I hope you're more fortunate than me. All mobs are safely aggrokited. After a while, I got so bored I charmed a coterie vampire with ToB to assist me with the killing (while hasted they lifetap a LOT and keep themselves healed). Anyway, locations of the camp from map:<br /><br />Camp 1 (DSP): appr. 1000, 800<br />Camp 2 (akheva 1): appr. 250, -1250<br />Camp 3 (akheva 2): appr. -400, -1400<br />Camp 4 (akheva 3): appr. -1500, -1500<br /><br /><a href="http://www.eqmaps.com/m3/maiden3.jpg" target="_blank">http://www.eqmaps.com/m3/maiden3.jpg</a><br /><br />References:<br /><br /><blockquote id="quote"><font size="2" face="arial" id="quote">quote:<hr height="1" noshade id="quote">After a long time in ME i figured out how to do this, but i advise you to log on early in the morning to avoide trains ant the zone wall near DP, i chose the camp with the 3 mobs near DP cause here it was possible to split them, and i was safe for ads once i had pulled the to zone wall. In the camp there are 3 mobs, and if Seer spawns you also have to deal with 2 goranga scouts.<hr height="1" noshade id="quote"></blockquote id="quote"></font id="quote"><br /><br />5. Katta/Sanctus Sery<br /><br />I got mine in Katta. Took me three kills. Helped several friends get theirs too. Drops VERY frequently in Katta. Zone in from Tenebrous, and head straight out. From there, you'll see a big courtyard to your west (near 0,-500). Go in there, buff up, get pet. Your target is the centurions. They summon, so have your pet (61 or 65 one) tank, while you heal it and dot the centurion. They're easily single pulled as they wander around the courtyard. Like I said, shard drops frequently here, about 1 in 4 kills.<br /><br />Campspot on map is near -400,-500 or whatever you prefer.<br /><br /><a href="http://www.eqmaps.com/m3/katta2.gif" target="_blank">http://www.eqmaps.com/m3/katta2.gif</a><br /><br />References:<br /><br /><blockquote id="quote"><font size="2" face="arial" id="quote">quote:<hr height="1" noshade id="quote">Sanctus Seru - A Legionneer of the Hand. Here there are 2 options, you can kill them at zone in or every guard walking on the wall surrounding the city. They con blue at lvl 60, but i pulled with darkness and agro kited with pet, my faction was ally at the beginning cause of a long time in Katta, and i think i killed 35 guards before shard drop, sitenote here is that the legionneer drops between 15 and 20 plat every time. But also an easy camp.<hr height="1" noshade id="quote"></blockquote id="quote"></font id="quote"><br /><br /><blockquote id="quote"><font size="2" face="arial" id="quote">quote:<hr height="1" noshade id="quote">Katta guards that drop the shards are your best bet. They drop maybe 1/5 kills, and they are pretty weak for the most part. They summon, but just let the pet build up agro and FD off any you might put on with dots and it shouldn't be much of a problem.<hr height="1" noshade id="quote"></blockquote id="quote"></font id="quote"><br /><br />6. Akheva ruins<br /><br />Yet another easy shard. You can get the shard off shaded stones, and they drop it frequently. Zone in, buff up, invis, head straight out, past the pillarroom (first room), into the second room. While entering the second room, you will set off a trap. When this happens, FD and wait for trap mobs to despawn. Get up, invis, and go to the soutwest corner of this room. There you'll see a little alien mob. This guy you root cook to death, piece of cake, here is your camp spot (appr. -100,200). I've never been there long enough to see him respawn, but I'm told he's on a 20 minute timer, so keep an eye out. From here, just wait til a shaded stone appears in the room. Pull him with darkness. If you get adds, just FD, wait for them to reset, and bring the darknessed shaded stone to camp, where you root cook him. Shard drops very frequently.<br /><br /><a href="http://www.eqmaps.com/m3/akheva1.jpg" target="_blank">http://www.eqmaps.com/m3/akheva1.jpg</a> (appr. loc. 1100,-900)<br /><br />References:<br /><br /><blockquote id="quote"><font size="2" face="arial" id="quote">quote:<hr height="1" noshade id="quote">Those are very annoying, because the chain agro like hell, zone in and invis then run straiht, then you come to an open room and keep running straight, and before you enter the next big room stop up because here there is a trap on the floor, so wakl very slowly and then you will get a message, it says something like yada yada is comming up from the floor. <br /><br />Now you have to flee back to the zone and zone out, and you can do this with out letting the mobs hit on you. Zone back in and run back to the trap, and now the trap is releached so it wont spawn again, i think its respawns every 30 min. When you enter the big room look left, there is a lillte crack or place in the left corner where there is a mob. Root dot this mob, because this is gonna be you pull spot. It will respawn every 20 min. Until you have killed this mob watch out for roamers. Now you are ready to pull the Stones, but be carefull because they have a huge agro range, AND you will get more then 1 when you pull, bu after some FD`s you have the stone close to you without any agro from his friends. This is hard and it took me 8 kills before the shard dropped. And alot of deaths.<hr height="1" noshade id="quote"></blockquote id="quote"></font id="quote"><br /><br />7. Fungus grove<br /><br />Shiknar Warriors. Also fairly easy, but can be somewhat dangerous if you don't look out. Invis, go to the shiknar tunnels, which are close to the Twilight Seas zonein. The tunnelmouth is near 2300,1300. Go into the cave and hug left untill you get to a room with some shiknar warriors a shiknar priest and some misc. mobs. I don't have a map of this spot, so I'll try to explain in details. When you enter the room, there is a small passage near the wall to the left. This is a safespot. From here, you can pull warriors and the priest. Kill the priest first, since this spot is within his healing-range. I root cooked all mobs, including the priest, whom you might want to finish off with a couple of nukes to prevent him from healing too much. Sometimes you get an add when pulling, so just split with darkness/FD. Be carefull of the mobs getting too close.<br /><br /><a href="http://www.eqmaps.com/m3/fungusgrove1.jpg" target="_blank">http://www.eqmaps.com/m3/fungusgrove1.jpg</a><br /><br />References:<br /><br /><blockquote id="quote"><font size="2" face="arial" id="quote">quote:<hr height="1" noshade id="quote">They can be a bit hard to find, but here is where you have to go.Important ( remember to invis) Run into their nest, turn left the first time you can and run straight through the big room, then you will enter a new big room, make a left turn again and you will enter a new room with the warriors. <br />In here there is also a Shik`Nar cleric, and a good advise is to kill this first because he will heal the others when the get low, i was so pissed cause it took me some time to figured this out. Anyway, in here there is a very small safe spot, when you enter the room, there is a little path and that is your safespot. This is a simple root dot camp, but KEEP the warrior rotted all the time otherwise you will run out of space to keep safe, because if you go to far back you will agro the others in the other room. When i did the shard the Shik`Nar Warlord was up, but i just killed him the same way. They will agro here so keep FD up, so u can split them, so pull with darkness and FD and wait to the others have returned to their spawns. I killed 10 warriors before the shard dropped.<hr height="1" noshade id="quote"></blockquote id="quote"></font id="quote"><br /><br />8. Acrylia caverns<br /><br />This shard is somewhat harder, but still fairly easy. Shard drops from a sanctum bloodguard. This guard does spawn near entrance, but doesn't always drop the shard, and is a rare spawn. For best droprate, do the inner part of the zone. Invis up, and zone in. Watch out for mobs that see invis. Turn right, go straight, and take the second turn on your left. Following that tunnel you'll come to a big room, with some skellies guarding the entrance to the castle. Obviously, these see through invis, and from here, you have two options. Get a pet and kill the skellies, or ITU past them. Whatever you choose should get you into the castle. In here, you'll see a statue. When you click it, it'll take you to the inner sanctum part of AC. At the very same spot you end up after clicking the statue is your camp spot. Two mobs wander through here, so watch their pathing, get up pet when the timing is right and kill them. Then you can pull random single mobs, and kill away using pet tanking untill a shard drops, which it does rather frequently.<br /><br />Campspot is marked as appr. -300,250 on the map.<br /><br /><a href="http://www.eqmaps.com/m3/acrylia1.jpg" target="_blank">http://www.eqmaps.com/m3/acrylia1.jpg</a><br /><br />References:<br /><br /><blockquote id="quote"><font size="2" face="arial" id="quote">quote:<hr height="1" noshade id="quote">You can invis all the way to the area with the 8 skellies sometimes. Some of the mobs on the way can spawn see invis though, and there are a LOT of casters. I just took the extra 1/2 hour to kill everything on the way.<br /><br />There is a wandering grimling that paths out to the skellies. Once he's gone, and 6 or so of the skellies, I suspended minion and ran through to the statue you click on. Some of these other guys can see invis too so you may have to take them out. Everthing that saw invis the 2 times I've done this was far enough away to not aggro.<br /><br />The port-in spot may or may not be hot. There are 2 wanderers that path into the room and 1 that paths close but won't aggro (even if fighting in the room). I believe any of these mobs can spawn see invis back here. The 2 wanderers are on different paths/timing so they can be in the same spot at the same time. Eventually they'll separate, and if they are separate eventually they will come back together.<br /><br />I recommend a little recon and patience when you get back there. Let the 2 wanderers get split up a bit and kill them first. You are then home free for the duration of the camp.<br /><br />I pet tanked 'em with LoZ and ToD... no problems. 20 min spawn timer. If you pull from the direction looking down the stairs, I never got more than 1 at a time. If you clear the room at the back with the guy on the pedestal it may then be kitable ground. I had heard it was a fairly common drop, so I didn't bother with trying to optimize throughput. Dropped in about 45 min.<hr height="1" noshade id="quote"></blockquote id="quote"></font id="quote"><br /><br />9. The Deep<br /><br />This one is somewhat tricky. I heavily recommend getting a map unless you know The Deep well. The tricky part isn't killing the shardropping mobs, but getting to them. This is the way I did it. Bind in shadow haven at the entrance to the southern echo caves. Buff up. Go to PoK. Find a friendly cleric and get virtue (not required, but nice to have). Then, find a friendly bard, and have him play the 2,5 minute bard song. When it pulses, gate. Run screaming through echo caverns and zone into the deep. Invis, and run to the pit. Pop QVoX, drop down. Feign and /q to clear aggro. Now you've done the hard part. Near the southern part of the pit is a way up. Invis and follow up. Some mobs on the way will see invis, but keep a good distance from them and you should be fine. Keep following the ledge untill you see the thought horrors, which are you mobs of target. The camp is located at appr. 750,250 on the map.<br /><br />Now, get a pet, buff up. Pull the mobs with darkness, at least the first 5 are single pullable. Dot them and run out of their line of vision. They will follow, when they are in safe distance from the rest of the mobs, send in pet and kite him around untill he's dead. Rinse repeat, loot shard, which drops fairly often.<br /><br /><a href="http://www.eqmaps.com/m3/thedeep2.jpg" target="_blank">http://www.eqmaps.com/m3/thedeep2.jpg</a><br /><br />References:<br /><br /><blockquote id="quote"><font size="2" face="arial" id="quote">quote:<hr height="1" noshade id="quote">Just Sow and Invis is enough to get to the bridge, a few mobs will see thru invis, but if you run fast enough they won't even agro, if they do agro just FD the agro, wait, re-invis and continue. No need to jump. (have a map with the bridge traced on it, makes it easy to cross)<br /><br />I set up camp right before the Horror Guard hallway, they come single and I pet tanked them.<br />the 2 at the top of the ramp in the tunnel would not always come single, the rest came single.<hr height="1" noshade id="quote"></blockquote id="quote"></font id="quote"><br /><br />10. Ssra<br /><br />This one is tricky, but doable. Still working on it myself, so I'll just quote Chiz.<br /><br />References:<br /><br /><blockquote id="quote"><font size="2" face="arial" id="quote">quote:<hr height="1" noshade id="quote">What AA's I had to make this work easier: IVU, Suspend 2, Pet Mend, Pet Hold.<br /><br />Grab some mage stuff before you head down there, at least 2 sets. Once at the mining cart, get 1st pet out, haste him, hand him the mage stuff and suspend him. IVU up and go through on the left tunnel into you come to a wall with a torch in the middle and two skels on either side. This is you pull spot and the 1st two skels are easy. Slow one, Mez other, unsuspend pet and let him tank with some heals here and there. Keep one mezzed. When he dies, kill other. Now you will look across and see only one skel, but he is linked to one on his left and one on his right side.<br /><br />No problem, but whatever you do, DO NOT MEZZ him and have the other two come. When Mez breaks, he brings two more with him because it seems like that is how it works down here. Did that 5 times in a row and noticed it worked the same time every time.<br /><br />So, instead pull him with slow, and then send pet on him, mez the other two, and keep killing. From there, always pull from the right and just repeat. Sometimes a named will spawn and that is where pet hold/mend comes in handy because you can fd split him from the rest with patience. Watch the respawn and then you are GTG.<hr height="1" noshade id="quote"></blockquote id="quote"></font id="quote"><br /><br />--- The rest ---<br /><br />Combine shards in shard container, which yields a new container. In here you put a rift, which can be looted from the small snakes you kill on emperor raids, and a orb of luclinite, which drops of most luclin bosses (including Grieg). Voila, you're keyed for VT :-)<br /></span></font></td>
