                <td bgcolor="#ECECEC" valign="top"><font color="#000000" face="arial" size="2"><small>Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;11/21/2003&nbsp;: 8:35:20 PM</small><hr size="2"><span class="spnMessageText"> Hi,<br /><br />will be updating this my own shard hunting experiences.<br /><br />DSP:  Took three clearing before my shard dropped.  I killed everything but the one guy who "flips over" the caves to Sambatas.<br /><br />ME:  Killed the three camps near ME (actually, two - I was clearing a third camp but I believe that is was an incorrect one... I didn't go by the locs above, just what seemed close... but leaving after getting my shard I saw another camp that might have been one of the ones mentioned in the guide).  At any rate, it took me about 3.5 hours camping in ME, fighting and killing non-stop (PH's, adds, etc.).  I lost one pet to adds, which  could have avoided if I had been paying more attention.  Named mob was a goranga prophet, easily resisted all nukes but lure - which didn't go through force shield.  Most of the time I was out of his casting range though.<br /><br />One other shard in bank from hunting a long time ago, but I don't know from where  :)  I'm thinking Scarlet Desert plateau since I went there to hunt once.  Will have to get it identified.  [Confirmed with identify - was SD shard... got it within one clearing of tower since I only did it once before getting bored].<br /><br />FG:  Got it on the third clearing.  Easy root rot, even with the named warlord guy (who was a bit of a pain with healing, etc.).<br /><br />Deep:  Longest shard camp for me so far.  Killed hundreds of horrors across the bridge.  Eventually got it after like 3 hours of clearing.<br /><br />Also, trying to go from the Deep to Ssra mines is harder than it looks - elders hit for 500+.  I had QVoX on and figured that I would pop it if I needed it (didn't know they hit that hard), and I was stunned long before I could even think about popping it =)  Going to try again but this time with QVoX on before I even see one of those elders.<br /><br />New edit:  Ok, so with SoW and both HS and QVoX I made it past  all the elders and THO (had no idea he was there, LOL) and zoned into the Ssra mines.  This is not a good idea if you don't know much about the mines (which I didn't).  To get to the actual spot where the skellies spawn you need to click through this wall type portal - which happens to be one way.  So you show up in a room of skellies.  Thankfully improved ITU lasts as long as you need it to to find a good spot to gate out of.<br /><br />The Grey:  Piece of cake.  Cleared the lake once and the second repop skellie had it.<br /><br />New Update:<br />Acrylia:  Summoned pet at ZI, suspended, went to statue and clicked in (killed the skellies on the way).  First mob that roamed by dropped the shard.  I was actually impatient and engaged him only to find out that the other roamer was inc.  Two was pretty hairy, but it all worked out (thank god for ToL and pet heal crits... pet was hurting by the time I ngot add pulled away and rooted).<br /><br />Katta:  went into the courtyard, got it off the seventh centurion I killed.  Next up, AR and Ssra!<br /><br />New edit:<br />Alright, just did Akheva.  Set up where the guide suggests to, kill the guy.  Invis up and run around to that hall to trip traps.  Once you've tripped em and are safe, pull shaded stones to the corner area that the alien guy was in.  Never got an add.  Dropped after about 6 kills.  Next up, Ssra!<br /><br />Cheers,<br />Merc</span></font></td>
